Topics:Inner Classes

What is inner class?
An inner class is a class which is defined inside of an outer class.
Syntax:
class Outer{
class Inner{
//stmts
}
}

Example:
class Outer {
    int outerData = 10;
    class Inner {
        void display() {
            System.out.println("Outer data = " + outerData);
        }
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Outer outer = new Outer();
        Outer.Inner inner = outer.new Inner();
        inner.display();
    }
}
